<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ861205-0092 </DOCNO><HL> Who's News:Thompson Medical's ChiefTo Add Post of President</HL><DD> 12/05/86</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> TM WNEWS </IN><DATELINE> NEW YORK  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Thompson Medical Co. said its chairman and chief executive officer will assume the additional post of president in connection with the year-end retirement of three top officers.    The health-care products company said its president, Moses Ratowsky, 67 years old, will retire. His duties will be assumed by the chairman, S. Daniel Abraham, 63, who remains chief executive. Edward L. Steinberg, 67, will give up the title of corporate secretary but remain vice chairman, and Jack W. Cox, 69, will retire as executive vice president. All three remain directors.    The company named Louis J. Guerci, 42, as executive vice president, finance and operations. He had been vice president, finance, and treasurer. A new position, executive vice president, marketing and sales, will be filled shortly, officials said. </TEXT></DOC>